636
00:36:30.012 --> 00:36:33.392
And currently, there's well over four million breast cancer survivors today, with

637
00:36:33.412 --> 00:36:36.372
that number projected to be growing every single year from here on out.

638
00:36:36.762 --> 00:36:40.702
It's estimated that about 70 to 80% of all cases are hormone receptor positive, and

639
00:36:40.732 --> 00:36:44.482
so this means that tumor growth is being stimulated by a patient's own estrogen or

640
00:36:44.572 --> 00:36:48.512
progesteroneIn the common sort of treatment pathway, at least for kind

641
00:36:48.532 --> 00:36:51.952
of early-stage hormone receptor-positive breast cancer, is that shortly after

642
00:36:51.972 --> 00:36:55.672
diagnosis, patients go through surgery followed by chemotherapy or

643
00:36:55.692 --> 00:36:57.372
radiation therapy whenever indicated.

644
00:36:57.392 --> 00:37:00.712
And then from there, for the next five to 10 years, they're on endocrine therapies

645
00:37:00.772 --> 00:37:02.571
to prevent the cancer from coming back.

646
00:37:02.592 --> 00:37:06.552
And as the presentation title suggests, we'll be focusing on endocrine therapies

647
00:37:06.612 --> 00:37:07.432
for this presentation.

648
00:37:08.512 --> 00:37:10.462
Currently, there are two main types of endocrine therapies.

649
00:37:10.492 --> 00:37:14.192
The first one being aromatase inhibitors, or AIs for short, and these function by

650
00:37:14.212 --> 00:37:15.952
preventing estrogen production in the body.

651
00:37:16.362 --> 00:37:19.472
And then the second one being tamoxifen, or TAM for short, and these function by

652
00:37:19.512 --> 00:37:22.792
blocking estrogen from attaching to cancer cells.

653
00:37:23.152 --> 00:37:26.612
And currently, nowadays, AIs tend to be a bit more commonly prescribed, but the

654
00:37:26.652 --> 00:37:30.612
selection between the two largely depends on patients based on cancer risk,

655
00:37:30.652 --> 00:37:33.932
on a patient and clinician preferences, as well as a patient's kind of baseline

656
00:37:33.952 --> 00:37:37.512
menopausal status as well. And both therapies have been shown to be

657
00:37:37.772 --> 00:37:41.522
incredibly efficacious. They substantially improve survival, at the same time, they

658
00:37:41.572 --> 00:37:44.632
substantially reduce the opportunity for cancer reoccurrences.

659
00:37:44.672 --> 00:37:47.612
But they definitely have their fair share of side effects, and so both therapies

660
00:37:47.632 --> 00:37:50.872
are associated with increased hot flashes, fatigue, and joint pain.

661
00:37:51.392 --> 00:37:54.192
In the case of aromatase inhibitors, they tend to have a bit more severe side

662
00:37:54.232 --> 00:37:57.472
effects in that they're associated with increased bone loss that can lead to hip

663
00:37:57.512 --> 00:38:00.512
fractures, and as well as potential cardiovascular disease risk, which is sort of

664
00:38:00.552 --> 00:38:02.272
the main focus of this project here.

665
00:38:02.772 --> 00:38:06.212
And then tamoxifen has actually been shown to be somewhat cardioprotective as well,

666
00:38:06.292 --> 00:38:09.832
which is interesting. And overall, because of the various side effects

667
00:38:09.872 --> 00:38:13.052
associated with both therapies, adherence varies widely across studies and

668
00:38:13.112 --> 00:38:17.092
settings. Some studies report five-year adherence as low as 20%, others as

669
00:38:17.192 --> 00:38:20.652
high as 80%. And so for this study, we sort of want to leverage the wide

670
00:38:20.692 --> 00:38:24.372
variation in adherence to assess how different sort of endocrine therapy

671
00:38:24.412 --> 00:38:28.192
durations of use or how different kind of endocrine therapy types are shaping kind

672
00:38:28.212 --> 00:38:31.252
of long-term cardiometabolic health among breast cancer survivors.

673
00:38:31.562 --> 00:38:35.132
And we hope that this work can provide a better picture of how these two therapies

674
00:38:35.172 --> 00:38:38.812
are kind of impacting downstream cardiovascular disease risk among the growing

675
00:38:40.672 --> 00:38:42.032
breast cancer survivor population.

