1547
01:26:06.004 --> 01:26:09.544
And just to briefly introduce Trop-2, our target

1548
01:26:09.604 --> 01:26:13.404
antigen, which is a type I transmembrane glycoprotein

1549
01:26:13.484 --> 01:26:16.864
that's involved in a number of different intracellular signaling pathways,

1550
01:26:17.404 --> 01:26:21.384
including proliferation, migration, and invasion of cancer cells.

1551
01:26:22.024 --> 01:26:25.464
And overexpression of Trop-2 correlates with poor prognosis

1552
01:26:25.764 --> 01:26:29.144
in a number of different tumor types, including urothelial,

1553
01:26:29.564 --> 01:26:33.404
non-small cell lung cancer, and gastric, as well as breast cancer.

1554
01:26:34.144 --> 01:26:37.394
Now, there are a few Trop-2 targeting ADCs currently on the

1555
01:26:37.424 --> 01:26:41.004
market for these indications. However, we believe this new

1556
01:26:41.124 --> 01:26:44.744
iADC platform provides a new potential

1557
01:26:44.784 --> 01:26:45.724
benefit over those.

1558
01:26:46.684 --> 01:26:50.484
ASP2998, or I'll refer to 2998 for

1559
01:26:50.504 --> 01:26:53.984
shorthand in this presentation, is a humanized IgG1 against

1560
01:26:54.004 --> 01:26:56.624
Trop-2 that carries two distinct payloads.

1561
01:26:57.224 --> 01:27:01.184
One is a topoisomerase I inhibitor, your typical cytotoxic

1562
01:27:01.244 --> 01:27:05.044
payload. The second is a STING agonist to induce

1563
01:27:05.084 --> 01:27:08.524
innate immunity through the STING pathway.

1564
01:27:08.554 --> 01:27:12.104
And what we believe is the mechanism of action is illustrated here on the right.

1565
01:27:12.624 --> 01:27:13.404
I think I have a pointer here.

1566
01:27:14.384 --> 01:27:18.084
So in a four-step process, the ADC

1567
01:27:18.684 --> 01:27:22.634
interacts with Trop-2 positive tumor cells, is internalized, and

1568
01:27:22.684 --> 01:27:26.564
causes cytotoxicity of those tumor cells through the topoisomerase

1569
01:27:26.604 --> 01:27:27.304
I payload.

1570
01:27:28.364 --> 01:27:31.894
As the cell is dying, we get immunogenic cell death and

1571
01:27:31.944 --> 01:27:35.504
release of a number of different molecules, including the STING agonist.

1572
01:27:36.104 --> 01:27:39.934
The STING agonist then is taken up by the surrounding innate immune cells as

1573
01:27:39.964 --> 01:27:40.934
well as T cells,

1574
01:27:41.864 --> 01:27:45.394
leading to further augmentation of the immune response,

1575
01:27:45.844 --> 01:27:49.824
priming of de novo T cell responses, ultimately turning, hopefully,

1576
01:27:49.924 --> 01:27:53.864
this tumor from cold to hot and leading to greater

1577
01:27:53.874 --> 01:27:57.144
anti-tumor efficacy and hopefully sustained tumor

1578
01:27:57.204 --> 01:28:00.284
immunity to give us a longer progression-free survival.

1579
01:28:01.804 --> 01:28:05.644
So to jump into the data, first looking in vitro, we

1580
01:28:05.704 --> 01:28:09.624
see a substantial benefit of adding a STING agonist to this ADC.

1581
01:28:10.304 --> 01:28:14.124
So this is a set of studies using the H292 cells, which are

1582
01:28:14.144 --> 01:28:18.093
Trop-2 positive, co-cultured with human PBMCs, and

1583
01:28:18.124 --> 01:28:21.504
then increasing amounts of 2998 or either of two

1584
01:28:21.604 --> 01:28:23.204
traditional Trop-2

1585
01:28:24.024 --> 01:28:27.864
cytotoxic-only ADCs. And what we see on the upper left

1586
01:28:27.904 --> 01:28:31.524
there in the cytotoxicity is a substantial shift in potency to the left with

1587
01:28:31.564 --> 01:28:34.324
2998 in the presence of these PBMCs.

1588
01:28:35.144 --> 01:28:38.184
And in those PBMCs, we see activation of the monocytes,

1589
01:28:39.024 --> 01:28:42.744
a hint of activation of the DCs, although they were few in number, and this is

1590
01:28:42.804 --> 01:28:45.884
indicative by CD86 upregulation.

1591
01:28:45.924 --> 01:28:49.804
We also see CD69 being turned on on both the CD4

1592
01:28:49.824 --> 01:28:52.264
and CD8 T cells, as well as the NK cells.

1593
01:28:52.304 --> 01:28:55.503
So we see broad immune cell activation in this system.

1594
01:28:56.484 --> 01:29:00.064
In addition, and in the same studies, we see release of a number of different

1595
01:29:00.084 --> 01:29:03.234
effector molecules, cytokines, and chemokines,

1596
01:29:03.744 --> 01:29:07.164
including IL-1 beta and IP-10. They're on the left, which are

1597
01:29:07.304 --> 01:29:11.024
canonical downstream of STING agonism, as well as

1598
01:29:11.224 --> 01:29:14.804
more distal effector molecules like interferon gamma and TNF.

1599
01:29:15.524 --> 01:29:19.384
Now, in this complex PBMC milieu, we do see production of

1600
01:29:19.504 --> 01:29:20.184
IL-6.

1601
01:29:21.204 --> 01:29:24.444
It is relatively low compared to what we would see with a T cell engager.

1602
01:29:24.984 --> 01:29:28.684
And importantly, we do not see IL-6 if we just incubate

1603
01:29:28.704 --> 01:29:32.584
PBMCs with 2998 in the absence of a Trop-2.

1604
01:29:32.644 --> 01:29:35.924
So this is tumor dependent and relatively low amounts of IL-6.

1605
01:29:38.524 --> 01:29:40.504
When we go in vivo and looking at the,

1606
01:29:41.464 --> 01:29:43.324
in this case, we're using an MC38

1607
01:29:44.124 --> 01:29:46.164
line overexpressing human Trop-2,

1608
01:29:47.464 --> 01:29:51.424
setting up these tumor models, and then treating either with vehicle or one of two

1609
01:29:51.484 --> 01:29:55.204
doses of 2998. We see in the

1610
01:29:55.264 --> 01:29:59.164
tumor infiltrating lymphocytes, an increase in monocytes and their

1611
01:29:59.244 --> 01:30:00.284
activation status,

1612
01:30:01.244 --> 01:30:04.644
as well as a trend towards more DCs that are more

1613
01:30:04.684 --> 01:30:05.384
activated.

1614
01:30:06.244 --> 01:30:09.524
We see more NKs, and more of them are expressing granzyme B,

1615
01:30:10.164 --> 01:30:12.764
and more of the CD8 T cells are also expressing granzyme B.

1616
01:30:13.124 --> 01:30:16.324
So we're seeing turning on of the whole immune system in this

1617
01:30:16.404 --> 01:30:17.604
MC38 model.

1618
01:30:19.364 --> 01:30:23.354
Now what that means for the animals, so in a very similar set of studies,

1619
01:30:23.443 --> 01:30:27.344
in this case, when we inoculated with the MC38 Trop-2,

1620
01:30:27.384 --> 01:30:29.744
we waited until they were a fairly large size.

1621
01:30:29.804 --> 01:30:33.344
This is 500 cubic millimeters. And then giving a single

1622
01:30:33.444 --> 01:30:37.204
treatment of either 2998, shown in two

1623
01:30:37.244 --> 01:30:40.924
different dose levels here in the blue, or the traditional

1624
01:30:40.984 --> 01:30:44.864
Trop-2 topoisomerase ADCs shown

1625
01:30:44.904 --> 01:30:48.724
here. And what we see in this more challenging large MC38 model,

1626
01:30:49.154 --> 01:30:52.764
the traditional Trop-2 only ADCs have a very

1627
01:30:52.904 --> 01:30:56.364
minimal effect. Whereas at the same dose level

1628
01:30:56.424 --> 01:30:59.884
matched here in the dark blue, we see a substantial

1629
01:31:00.264 --> 01:31:01.984
control and actual tumor regression.

1630
01:31:02.374 --> 01:31:05.744
And even dosing down a little bit, we see tumor stasis.

1631
01:31:07.964 --> 01:31:10.984
Now what becomes very interesting is the prolonged immunity.

1632
01:31:11.344 --> 01:31:14.484
And this is one of the real value drivers of this platform.

1633
01:31:15.324 --> 01:31:18.774
So this is a longer set of experiments to look at, are we

