functions. In comparison to kinases that are well-studied and

1768
01:39:14.508 --> 01:39:17.918
targeted, which add phosphate groups to the residues of serine, threonine, and

1769
01:39:17.948 --> 01:39:18.828
tyrosine

1770
01:39:19.808 --> 01:39:23.408
for regulating protein activity, phosphatases remove the phosphate groups and are

1771
01:39:23.468 --> 01:39:27.428
just as critical for signaling pathways, but remain comparatively

1772
01:39:27.708 --> 01:39:30.768
unexplored. So for example, upon DNA damage,

1773
01:39:31.168 --> 01:39:34.468
ATR/ATM phosphorylate targets such as gamma H2AX

1774
01:39:35.168 --> 01:39:38.688
and EYA4, and phosphorylated EYA4 can dephosphorylate gamma

1775
01:39:38.788 --> 01:39:42.618
H2AX and RAD51, promoting repair through homologous recombination.

1776
01:39:42.628 --> 01:39:46.288
But when EYA4 is lost or depleted, cells become homologous

1777
01:39:46.328 --> 01:39:50.068
recombination deficient or HRD positive, and this results in cell

1778
01:39:50.148 --> 01:39:53.708
death. So triple-negative breast cancer is an aggressive

1779
01:39:53.808 --> 01:39:57.558
subtype of breast cancer with limited targeted therapies due to the lack of

1780
01:39:57.588 --> 01:40:00.708
estrogen receptor, progesterone receptor, and HER2

1781
01:40:00.888 --> 01:40:04.828
expression. And TNBC patients are more likely to

1782
01:40:04.848 --> 01:40:08.088
carry the BRCA1 or 2 mutations, with a prevalence of about 10% to

1783
01:40:08.168 --> 01:40:11.468
20%, representing a clinically significant

1784
01:40:11.708 --> 01:40:14.948
subset of patients who are HRD positive.

1785
01:40:15.568 --> 01:40:19.388
If we look broadly at genetic predispositions, BRCA1 or

1786
01:40:19.468 --> 01:40:23.048
2 account for a substantial fraction of these inherited mutations.

1787
01:40:23.148 --> 01:40:26.568
However, many tumors fall into the other mutations category,

1788
01:40:27.527 --> 01:40:30.188
highlighting this genetic heterogeneity of breast cancer.

1789
01:40:30.697 --> 01:40:34.228
And functionally, when genes such as BRCA1 or 2 are mutated,

1790
01:40:34.488 --> 01:40:38.228
cells lose their ability to repair double-strand breaks, which creates a

1791
01:40:38.248 --> 01:40:39.438
therapeutic vulnerability,

1792
01:40:40.388 --> 01:40:44.138
leading to therapies that can not only exploit preexisting HR deficiency,

1793
01:40:44.468 --> 01:40:46.148
but also attempt to actively induce it.

1794
01:40:47.348 --> 01:40:49.048
Potentially sensitizing

1795
01:40:49.868 --> 01:40:53.548
HR-proficient tumors to platinum-based chemotherapies or, for

1796
01:40:53.588 --> 01:40:57.188
example, the use of PARP inhibitors, and expand the population of

1797
01:40:57.508 --> 01:41:00.948
TNBC patients who could possibly benefit from these types of

1798
01:41:00.988 --> 01:41:04.688
treatments. So first we asked whether EYA4 is

1799
01:41:04.728 --> 01:41:07.568
epigenetically altered in TNBC, and with

1800
01:41:07.588 --> 01:41:11.508
methylation sequence analysis, and we

1801
01:41:11.548 --> 01:41:15.458
did around 30 patient samples, showing that EYA4 is hypermethylated

1802
01:41:15.968 --> 01:41:19.808
at the first intron-exon junction in TNBC compared to the

1803
01:41:19.868 --> 01:41:23.288
matched normal tissue. And then while DNA methylation is

1804
01:41:23.568 --> 01:41:27.238
classically associated with gene silencing, its effects are highly

1805
01:41:27.268 --> 01:41:30.858
context dependent. Prior studies and observations suggest that

1806
01:41:30.888 --> 01:41:34.537
EYA4 hypermethylation in this region may be

1807
01:41:34.568 --> 01:41:38.088
associated with increased expression rather than repression.

1808
01:41:38.588 --> 01:41:42.128
So we did analysis of a breast invasive carcinoma data set

1809
01:41:42.708 --> 01:41:45.428
showing that EYA4 alterations occur in approximately

1810
01:41:45.568 --> 01:41:49.428
2.8% of patients driven by mRNA upregulation.

1811
01:41:49.788 --> 01:41:53.768
And then we then validated this by assessing EYA4 expression across

1812
01:41:53.808 --> 01:41:57.348
breast cancer cell lines using QR-PCR and immunobloting,

1813
01:41:57.728 --> 01:42:00.658
and we see that the TNBC cell line,

1814
01:42:00.768 --> 01:42:02.068
MDAMB-231,

1815
01:42:03.048 --> 01:42:06.708
exhibits the highest endogenous EYA4 expression at both the transcript and

1816
01:42:06.848 --> 01:42:10.728
the protein level. So now that we know that EYA4 is

1817
01:42:10.928 --> 01:42:14.048
overexpressed in breast cancer, we asked whether it can contribute to something

1818
01:42:14.068 --> 01:42:17.988
like tumor progression and whether it could be a viable therapeutic target.

1819
01:42:18.648 --> 01:42:20.768
To address this, we used two in vivo models

1820
01:42:21.608 --> 01:42:23.208
with luciferase-labeled cancer cells,

1821
01:42:24.248 --> 01:42:26.628
where tumor burden can be monitored with

1822
01:42:27.548 --> 01:42:28.588
bioluminescent signaling.

1823
01:42:29.808 --> 01:42:32.648
In this system, light emission correlates with the number of the viable tumor

1824
01:42:32.728 --> 01:42:36.468
cells. So in the top panel, EYA4 was overexpressed in MCF7

1825
01:42:36.488 --> 01:42:36.768
cells,

1826
01:42:37.968 --> 01:42:41.068
which were injected orthotopically into the mammary fat pad.

1827
01:42:41.648 --> 01:42:44.628
And this represents a primary tumor xenograft model.

1828
01:42:45.468 --> 01:42:49.108
Here, EYA4 expression leads to a significant increase in the

1829
01:42:49.128 --> 01:42:52.308
bioluminescent signal over time, indicating tumor growth.

1830
01:42:52.848 --> 01:42:56.648
And visibly, these tumors are larger in volume, confirming that EYA4

1831
01:42:56.658 --> 01:42:58.788
promotes the primary tumor growth in vivo.

1832
01:42:59.328 --> 01:43:02.808
And then in this bottom panel, we used a tail vein metastasis model with

1833
01:43:02.908 --> 01:43:06.368
TNBC cells where EYA4 was depleted using

1834
01:43:06.488 --> 01:43:09.868
shRNA. And loss of EYA4 results in the reduction in the

1835
01:43:09.888 --> 01:43:13.808
bioluminescent signaling. Through histological analysis of the lung

1836
01:43:13.868 --> 01:43:17.568
tissue, we confirmed a reduction in metastatic lesions as well as

1837
01:43:17.628 --> 01:43:20.588
the foci. And thus, we can

1838
01:43:22.008 --> 01:43:25.898
see that EYA4 is not only sufficient to drive tumor growth, but

1839
01:43:25.968 --> 01:43:27.988
also it is required for metastasis.

1840
01:43:29.448 --> 01:43:32.908
We next explored how EYA4 functions at the molecular level,

1841
01:43:33.228 --> 01:43:36.628
specifically in maintaining genomic stability under replication stress.

1842
01:43:36.848 --> 01:43:38.428
To assess the DNA damage, we

1843
01:43:40.028 --> 01:43:43.868
measured with the gamma H2AX. It's a well-established marker for DNA

1844
01:43:43.928 --> 01:43:47.888
damage, double-strand breaks. H2AX is a variant of the histone H2A

1845
01:43:47.948 --> 01:43:51.848
protein, and upon DNA damage, it becomes phosphorylated at the serine

1846
01:43:51.948 --> 01:43:55.648
139 residue to form gamma H2AX. And it then

1847
01:43:55.688 --> 01:43:59.528
accumulates at the sites of DNA damage at these discrete nuclear foci,

1848
01:44:00.088 --> 01:44:03.368
which can be visualized using the immunofluorescent staining.

1849
01:44:04.408 --> 01:44:08.268
And then in EYF4-depleted cells, we see an increase in gamma H2AX

1850
01:44:08.288 --> 01:44:10.328
foci, shown here in red.

1851
01:44:11.328 --> 01:44:15.188
The accumulation of these foci indicates unresolved DNA damage rather than

1852
01:44:15.688 --> 01:44:19.164
efficient repair.Given that the loss of EYF4 leads to

1853
01:44:19.484 --> 01:44:23.424
this increase in DNA damage, we next asked how EYF4 functions at the

1854
01:44:23.484 --> 01:44:24.264
site of

1855
01:44:25.344 --> 01:44:28.774
damaged DNA. So to test this, we wanted to see whether

1856
01:44:28.804 --> 01:44:31.124
EYF4 directly binds DNA. We've

1857
01:44:32.264 --> 01:44:36.204
used microscale thermophoresis or MST to quantify

1858
01:44:36.224 --> 01:44:38.344
binding interactions and measure affinity.

1859
01:44:38.704 --> 01:44:42.324
We found that EYF4 binds single-strand DNA with affinity in the nanomolar

1860
01:44:42.384 --> 01:44:46.244
range. And when we introduce a phosphomimetic mutation,

1861
01:44:46.764 --> 01:44:50.613
we see that the DNA binding is significantly reduced.

1862
01:44:51.364 --> 01:44:54.964
In the SQ/TQ motif, this is a consensus site for ATR/ATM

1863
01:44:54.984 --> 01:44:58.944
phosphorylation. And then looking at their protein structure in the N-terminal

1864
01:44:58.984 --> 01:45:02.284
region of EYF4, we see that there are features such as a basic tail

1865
01:45:02.744 --> 01:45:06.504
in that span of amino acids and also an AT-hook-like

1866
01:45:06.564 --> 01:45:08.864
motif, which are known to support DNA binding.

1867
01:45:08.944 --> 01:45:12.864
So currently, we're mapping this region further to see how these

1868
01:45:12.924 --> 01:45:16.284
are interacting with DNA. And we also performed

1869
01:45:16.304 --> 01:45:19.784
histone direct pull-down, followed by mass spec to identify

1870
01:45:19.824 --> 01:45:23.704
interactions with these chromatin-associated proteins, such as

1871
01:45:23.844 --> 01:45:27.704
H2AX. Normally, EYF4 would associate with chromatin, and then upon

1872
01:45:27.764 --> 01:45:30.544
DNA damage, becomes phosphorylated and then

1873
01:45:31.424 --> 01:45:35.324
it detaches, which reduces its DNA binding and releases it from chromatin, and then

1874
01:45:35.364 --> 01:45:38.004
EYF4 can then act on its downstream targets

1875
01:45:39.584 --> 01:45:43.344
or substrates. And then having shown that EYF4 is binding to

1876
01:45:43.384 --> 01:45:47.184
DNA and functions at the sites of DNA damage, we next asked whether its phosphatase

1877
01:45:47.224 --> 01:45:49.764
activity is also regulated in this context.

1878
01:45:50.244 --> 01:45:51.844
And so to do that, we

1879
01:45:53.124 --> 01:45:57.044
measured using a malachite green assay to quantify the release of free phosphate

1880
01:45:57.164 --> 01:45:59.274
as a readout of the phosphatase activity.

1881
01:45:59.664 --> 01:46:03.284
And we found that EYF4 exhibits phosphatase activity at the tyrosine 142

1882
01:46:03.904 --> 01:46:06.784
residue with minimal activity towards serine 139.

1883
01:46:07.104 --> 01:46:10.484
And then also in the presence of DNA, its activity is

1884
01:46:10.494 --> 01:46:14.444
significantly enhanced. And so this suggests that DNA

1885
01:46:15.304 --> 01:46:19.244
binding is not only localizing EYF4 to sites of damage, but it's

1886
01:46:19.304 --> 01:46:22.584
also directly stimulating its enzymatic activity.

1887
01:46:22.664 --> 01:46:26.584
And because this is a defined and measurable catalytic activity, it highlights

1888
01:46:26.624 --> 01:46:29.384
EYF4 as a potentially drugable target.

1889
01:46:30.384 --> 01:46:34.344
So we then investigated further whether EYF4 can be therapeutically targeted.

1890
01:46:35.024 --> 01:46:38.674
To assess HR, we looked at RAD51 phosphorylation with

1891
01:46:38.704 --> 01:46:41.684
immunofluorescence, and phosphorylated

1892
01:46:42.364 --> 01:46:45.884
RAD51 foci, shown in red, serves as a marker of HR

1893
01:46:45.904 --> 01:46:49.664
disruption. So upon depletion of EYF4, we observed a strong increase of

1894
01:46:49.704 --> 01:46:53.624
RAD51 foci indicating impaired function, disrupted HR.

1895
01:46:53.684 --> 01:46:57.524
And we identified a small molecule inhibitor, CIDd ending

1896
01:46:57.564 --> 01:47:00.224
in 89, as a top candidate from a drug screening.

1897
01:47:00.674 --> 01:47:04.024
And looking at this growth curve, treatment with this inhibitor most efficiently

1898
01:47:04.064 --> 01:47:07.984
suppresses growth compared to the control of the other candidates.

1899
01:47:09.084 --> 01:47:12.824
There's a reduction in cell viability measured

1900
01:47:12.864 --> 01:47:13.704
by

1901
01:47:14.844 --> 01:47:18.244
an

1902
01:47:20.224 --> 01:47:23.624
MTT assay, which is quantifying metabolic activity as a proxy

1903
01:47:23.704 --> 01:47:27.304
for viable cells, and then further showing this in a

1904
01:47:27.344 --> 01:47:31.174
dose-dependent curve with increasing concentrations of the inhibitor reducing

1905
01:47:31.184 --> 01:47:34.744
EYF4 activity. And then to directly measure HR, we use the

1906
01:47:34.784 --> 01:47:38.704
dRGFP system, the gene conversion assay, where a double-strand

1907
01:47:38.764 --> 01:47:42.484
break is induced, and then restoring by HR restores

1908
01:47:42.504 --> 01:47:46.184
GFP expression. So treatment with this inhibitor leads to a

1909
01:47:46.194 --> 01:47:48.584
dose-dependent decrease in GFP,

1910
01:47:49.404 --> 01:47:51.964
and a decrease in GFP positive cells indicating

1911
01:47:52.764 --> 01:47:54.544
reduced HR efficiency.

1912
01:47:55.724 --> 01:47:59.564
And so in conclusion, our data identifies EYF4 as promoting

1913
01:47:59.904 --> 01:48:03.884
a key regulator of HR and genome stability in TNBC and

1914
01:48:03.944 --> 01:48:07.264
supporting DNA repair, while its loss or inhibition

1915
01:48:07.304 --> 01:48:10.784
induces HR deficiency, DNA damage

1916
01:48:10.824 --> 01:48:14.124
accumulation, and reduced tumor cell survival, as well as

1917
01:48:14.884 --> 01:48:18.544
the pharmacological inhibition of phenocopies, a type of

1918
01:48:18.584 --> 01:48:22.474
genetic depletion, highlighting EYF4 as a potential target, and

1919
01:48:22.504 --> 01:48:25.664
potentially sensitizing TNBC to other

1920
01:48:25.884 --> 01:48:28.984
DNA-damaging therapeutic targeted therapies.

1921
01:48:30.164 --> 01:48:32.683
And lastly, I would like to acknowledge my mentors, Dr.

1922
01:48:32.724 --> 01:48:35.683
Eloise Dreher, lab members, and then not mentioned, but also

1923
01:48:36.584 --> 01:48:40.124
for my slides, Dmitry Kovalsky, Daruka Mohadevan, Stanley McCarvey,

1924
01:48:40.544 --> 01:48:44.084
Dong Xiao, the American Cancer Society, and my program directors, as well as

1925
01:48:44.124 --> 01:48:47.284
clinical mentor, Dr. Gail Tomlinson. Thank you.

1926
01:48:54.564 --> 01:48:56.184
Okay, I'll start.

1927
01:48:58.024 --> 01:48:58.204
So

1928
01:48:59.064 --> 01:49:02.154
we know that for PARP inhibitors,

1929
01:49:02.284 --> 01:49:03.924
BRCAness-

1930
01:49:04.384 --> 01:49:04.484
Yes

1931
01:49:05.324 --> 01:49:09.144
